N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 §§ 143-3.2 - XML format

State Regulations

The central filing office shall, from time to time, designate the XML format to be used as the format for transmission of XML
documents to the central filing office. The central filing office shall, at the
request of an authorized XML remitter, identify which versions and releases of
the XML format are then in use by and acceptable to the central filing
office. Notes
